'''Nestory Irankunda''' ({{IPA|en|nɛstəriː ɪrəŋkʊndɑ|}} {{respell|NEST-ər-EE irəng-KUN-da}}; {{IPA|rn|iɾaŋkunda|lang}}; born 9 February 2006) is a professional [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|Watford}} club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]. Born a Burundian refugee in Tanzania, he plays for the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]]. He is regarded as one of the best Australian players of his generation.

Irankunda played youth football for [[Adelaide Croatia Raiders SC|Adelaide Croatia Raiders]] before moving to [[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]] in 2021. He started his professional career when he signed a scholarship contract in September 2021, followed by his league debut in January 2022. He scored his first league goal the same year, becoming the second-youngest goalscorer in the competition. In March 2024, he scored his first [[hat-trick]], becoming the second youngest to do so in [[Soccer in Australia|Australia men's history]]. Irankunda joined Bayern Munich in 2024, breaking the A-League transfer record.<ref>{{cite web |title=A-League transfer fee shattered as teen prodigy Irankunda signs on with Bayern Munich |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-11-14/nestory-irankunda-to-join-german-giants-bayern-munich/103105996 |website=ABC News |access-date=18 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=18 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231118001827/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-11-14/nestory-irankunda-to-join-german-giants-bayern-munich/103105996 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Irankunda chose to represent Australia, whilst also being eligible for [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]] or [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]]. At the youth level, he helped lead [[Australia men's national under-17 soccer team|Australia U17]] to qualification for the [[AFC U-17 Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda: Who is Bayern Munich's Australian sensation? |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/nestory-irankunda-who-is-bayern-munich-s-australian-sensation-25335 |publisher=[[Bundesliga]] |access-date=18 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=18 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231118115928/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/nestory-irankunda-who-is-bayern-munich-s-australian-sensation-25335 |url-status=live }}</ref> After his first call-up for the seniors in March 2023 and debut in June 2024, Irankunda became the second-youngest Australian to score for his nation in a [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] ([[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2026]]) match.

Irankunda was ranked by [[CIES Football Observatory]] as one of the top 100 Under-20 players worldwide in 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Best teenagers: top 200 |url=https://football-observatory.com/WeeklyPost510 |website=CIES Football Observatory |access-date=30 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pisani |first1=Sacha |title=A-Leagues sensation & star graduate among top-100 teenagers in world football ft. Lamine Yamal |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/best-u20-players-lamine-yamal-barcelona-dylan-leonard-western-united-nestory-irankunda-watford-a-league-news/ |website=A-Leagues |date=27 August 2025 |access-date=30 August 2025}}</ref>

==Early life==
Nestory Irankunda was born on 9 February 2006<ref name=soccerway>{{cite web  | title= N. Irankunda  | website= Soccerway  | url= https://au.soccerway.com/players/nestory-irankunda/788183/  | access-date= 28 August 2023  | archive-date= 4 November 2023  | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20231104184302/https://au.soccerway.com/players/nestory-irankunda/788183/  | url-status= live  }}</ref> in [[Kigoma]], [[Tanzania]], the third eldest child with two older brothers and five younger sisters to Gideon, a [[ridesharing company|rideshare]] driver, and his wife, Dafroza.<ref name="sydneymorning">{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title=This 17-year-old schoolkid could be world class. Can Australian soccer help him get there? |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/this-17-year-old-schoolkid-could-be-world-class-can-australian-soccer-help-him-get-there-20230502-p5d4wk.html |website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230504082246/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/this-17-year-old-schoolkid-could-be-world-class-can-australian-soccer-help-him-get-there-20230502-p5d4wk.html |archive-date=4 May 2023 |date=4 May 2023}}</ref><ref name="canberratimes">{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Stage set for rising Adelaide star Irankunda to shine |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8182367/stage-set-for-rising-adelaide-star-irankunda-to-shine/ |website=[[The Canberra Times]] |date=3 May 2023 |access-date=16 May 2023 |archive-date=16 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230516120405/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8182367/stage-set-for-rising-adelaide-star-irankunda-to-shine/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="ref0">{{cite web |last=McGuire |first=Michael |title=Adelaide United's Nestory Irankunda heads for the big time with Bayern Munich |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/sport/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-heads-for-the-big-time-with-bayern-munich/news-story/e0e1a069e0cd5bb2853708c5c40bbae5?amp&nk=314dc2dd298b6281c09a97562a8a3636-1699959736 |website=Adelaide Now |publisher=The Advertiser |access-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231114110159/https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/sport/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-heads-for-the-big-time-with-bayern-munich/news-story/e0e1a069e0cd5bb2853708c5c40bbae5?amp&nk=314dc2dd298b6281c09a97562a8a3636-1699959736 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023}}</ref> His parents were originally from [[Burundi]], but fled their home due to the [[Burundi Civil War|civil war]] escalating at the time. His father led his family to a refugee camp in Tanzania where Nestory was born.<ref name="sydneymorning"/><ref name="canberratimes"/> They moved to [[Perth]] in [[Western Australia]], when Irankunda was three months old, before moving to the northern suburbs of [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]] in 2013.<ref name="codesports">{{cite web |last=Peacock |first=Adam |title=Adelaide United's Nestory Irankunda's remarkable power has caught the attention of the Socceroos and European clubs |url=https://www.codesports.com.au/football/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-remarkable-power-has-caught-the-attention-of-the-socceroos-and-european-clubs/news-story/2af5ceea7361a58d8bfd24ccd246c7cd |website=Code Sports |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230318024124/https://www.codesports.com.au/football/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-remarkable-power-has-caught-the-attention-of-the-socceroos-and-european-clubs/news-story/2af5ceea7361a58d8bfd24ccd246c7cd#selection-2157.0-2157.115 |archive-date=18 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Snape |first=Jack |title=Nestory Irankunda: how the 17-year-old sensation was snapped up by Bayern Munich |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/nov/16/nestory-irankunda-how-the-17-year-old-sensation-was-snapped-up-by-bayern-munich |website=The Guardian |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=15 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008063944/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/nov/16/nestory-irankunda-how-the-17-year-old-sensation-was-snapped-up-by-bayern-munich |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda grew up in a [[Christians|Christian]] home,<ref name="keepup2">{{cite web |last=Weiner |first=David |title=Why Nestory Irankunda picked Bayern over the EPL: 'There was a photo he showed me' |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-transfer-news-highlights-who-is-he/ |publisher=[[A-League]] |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115022827/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-transfer-news-highlights-who-is-he/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and found his love of football whilst playing with his older brothers in the yard of his home. At the age of eight, Irankunda played for his first football club at [[Parafield Gardens, South Australia|Parafield Gardens]] after being spotted by the under-10s coach of the local club.<ref name="sydneymorning"/><ref name="ref1">{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Matthew |title=Nestory Irankunda's signing with Bayern Munich is a 'watershed moment' for Australian soccer |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-11-15/nestory-irankunda-signing-with-bayern-munich/103107460 |website=ABC News |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=15 November 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115054353/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-11-15/nestory-irankunda-signing-with-bayern-munich/103107460 |url-status=live }}</ref>

During his junior years in Australian football, he played with Northern Wolves and Parafield Gardens before being scouted and signed by [[National Premier Leagues]] (NPL) side [[Adelaide Croatia Raiders SC|Adelaide Croatia Raiders]].<ref name="sydneymorning"/><ref name="theroar">{{cite web |title=The naïvety of Nestor: 15-year-old bursts on to the scene |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/02/01/the-naivety-of-nestor-15-year-old-bursts-on-to-the-scene/ |website=The Roar |date=31 January 2022 |access-date=16 May 2023 |archive-date=16 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230516120405/https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/02/01/the-naivety-of-nestor-15-year-old-bursts-on-to-the-scene/ |url-status=live }}</ref> During his time in the youth levels for the Raiders, he caught the attention of many scouts in the area including [[Airton Andrioli]], the head of youth for [[A-League]] side [[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]], who eventually invited him to trial for the youth squad before offering a permanent spot after a couple of weeks.<ref name="theroar"/><ref name="innersanctum">{{cite web |last=Pagonis |first=Antonis |title=Irankunda's rapid ascent from junior local football to A-League Men in two years |url=https://www.theinnersanctum.com.au/nestory-irankundas-rapid-ascent-adelaide-united/ |website=The Inner Sanctum |date=10 February 2022 |access-date=16 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032602/https://www.theinnersanctum.com.au/nestory-irankundas-rapid-ascent-adelaide-united/ |url-status=live }}</ref> When asked about Irankunda in an interview in 2023, Andrioli stated, "When you see a boy like Nestory, some players have that naturally. That gift of understanding and reading the game. Being street smart. You don’t see that a lot in Australian players. That's why Nestory from the start had that kind of thing."<ref name="keepup1">{{cite web |author1=Sachapisani |title=I discovered Nestory Irankunda after plotting 'mission impossible' against the Socceroos |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-finals-adelaide-united-preview-tickets-socceroos-nestory-irankunda/ |website=keepup.com |date=13 May 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517021932/https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-finals-adelaide-united-preview-tickets-socceroos-nestory-irankunda/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Adelaide United===
====2021–22: Development====
In his first year for Adelaide United, Irankunda initially played with the reserves, and after a couple of weeks, started featuring for [[Adelaide United FC Youth|Adelaide United NPL]] side.<ref name="innersanctum"/> Despite being 15 at the time, he accumulated 26 appearances and 12 goals in total for both the senior and reserve squad for the Reds.<ref name="innersanctum"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Nestor Irankunda - 2021 Player Statistics |url=https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?action=PSTATS&pID=204565555&client=0-10180-196417-577489-26636394 |website=GameDay |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032604/https://websites.mygameday.app/team_info.cgi?action=PSTATS&pID=204565555&client=0-10180-196417-577489-26636394 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 27 September 2021, Irankunda signed a scholarship contract (his first professional contract) with Adelaide United.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda signs scholarship deal with Reds |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-signs-scholarship-deal-with-reds |publisher=[[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]] |date=27 September 2021 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008063950/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-signs-scholarship-deal-with-reds/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 8 January 2022, at the age of 15 years and 333 days, Irankunda became the sixth youngest player in [[A-League Men|A-League]] history and the third youngest debutant at the time for Adelaide United when he made his debut against [[The Original Rivalry|rivals]] [[Melbourne Victory FC|Melbourne Victory]], drawing 1–1 at the [[Melbourne Rectangular Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |title=The 15-year-old phenomena lighting up the A-League Men |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/01/11/the-15-year-old-phenomena-lighting-up-the-a-league-men/ |website=The Roar |date=10 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032601/https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/01/11/the-15-year-old-phenomena-lighting-up-the-a-league-men/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Matthewcomito |title=The 10 youngest ALM teens and what happened next |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/the-10-youngest-alm-teens-and-what-happened-next/ |website=keepup.com |date=10 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032602/https://keepup.com.au/news/the-10-youngest-alm-teens-and-what-happened-next/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 30 January, Irankunda scored his first league goal, a [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] in stoppage time to win the game 2–1 against [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Mitchell |first=Alex |title=Fifteen-year-old Irankunda sparks Reds into dramatic comeback after free-kick |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/fifteen-year-old-irankunda-sparks-reds-into-dramatic-comeback-after-free-kick |publisher=Adelaide United |date=30 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008063945/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/fifteen-year-old-irankunda-sparks-reds-into-dramatic-comeback-after-free-kick/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Filosi |first=Gianluca |title=Irankunda discusses free-kick in 2-1 smash-and-grab win over Newcastle |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-discusses-free-kick-in-2-1-smash-and-grab-win-over-newcastle |publisher=Adelaide United |date=30 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008063945/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-discusses-free-kick-in-2-1-smash-and-grab-win-over-newcastle/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His goal made him the second youngest goalscorer in the league at the age of 15 years and 355 days, after [[Mohamed Toure (footballer, born 2004)|Mohamed Toure]] who scored at the age of 15 years and 325 days.<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=The 12 youngest scorers in Isuzu UTE A-League history & what happened next |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/the-12-youngest-scorers-in-isuzu-ute-a-league-history-what-happened-next/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231103010250/https://keepup.com.au/news/the-12-youngest-scorers-in-isuzu-ute-a-league-history-what-happened-next/ |archive-date=3 November 2023 |website=keepup.com |date=7 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Watch: Teen's stunner ignites shock Reds comeback |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/live-isuzu-ute-a-league-on-sunday-january-30-goals-highlights-video-scores-talking-points/ |website=keepup.com |date=30 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032604/https://keepup.com.au/news/live-isuzu-ute-a-league-on-sunday-january-30-goals-highlights-video-scores-talking-points/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=15yo steals the show with maiden A-League goal for Adelaide United |url=https://www.sen.com.au/news/2022/01/31/15yo-steals-the-show-with-maiden-a-league-goal-for-adelaide-united/ |website=sen.com |date=30 January 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032602/https://www.sen.com.au/news/2022/01/31/15yo-steals-the-show-with-maiden-a-league-goal-for-adelaide-united/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his second league goal, coming off the bench to score the winner in a 2–1 home win over [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] on 27 February.<ref>{{cite web |last=Filosi |first=Gianluca |title=Dream come true to score at Coopers Stadium says Irankunda |work=Adelaide United |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/dream-come-true-to-score-at-coopers-stadium-says-irankunda%ef%bf%bc |date=27 February 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517032605/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/dream-come-true-to-score-at-coopers-stadium-says-irankunda%EF%BF%BC |url-status=live }}</ref> On 24 April, he increased his goalscoring tally to three after he scored a stoppage time goal and helped his side secure a 2–0 win against [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Filosi |first=Gianluca |title=Irankunda 'surprised' by late Coopers goal |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-surprised-by-late-coopers-goal/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=14 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240414065227/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-surprised-by-late-coopers-goal/ |archive-date=14 April 2024 |date=25 April 2022}}</ref> His brief cameo won him the Tomas Dale Medal for his sporting manner in the club.<ref>{{cite web |last=Filosi |first=Gianluca |title=Irankunda 'surprised' by late Coopers goal |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-surprised-by-late-coopers-goal |publisher=Adelaide United |date=25 April 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008063946/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-surprised-by-late-coopers-goal/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 May, Irankunda was selected in the [[A-Leagues All Stars Game|A-Leagues All Stars]] squad, alongside teammates [[Isaías Sánchez]] and [[Alexandar Popovic]], to face Spanish giants [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Filosi |first=Gianluca |title=Reds trio feature against Barcelona |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/reds-trio-feature-against-barcelona |publisher=Adelaide United |date=25 May 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023}}</ref>

====2022–23: Breakthrough season====
In November 2022, Irankunda missed the first [[The Original Rivalry|Original Rivalry]] match of the [[2022–23 A-League Men|2022–23 season]] after receiving a month's suspension from the club for turning up late to several team meetings and avoiding "chores" associated with being one of the club’s younger players.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda suspension a lesson for all young players |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/11/17/irankunda-suspension-a-lesson-for-all-young-players/ |website=The Roar |date=16 November 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517150815/https://www.theroar.com.au/2022/11/17/irankunda-suspension-a-lesson-for-all-young-players/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda disappointed despite return to squad |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-disappointed-despite-return-to-squad |publisher=Adelaide United |date=9 December 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517150815/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-disappointed-despite-return-to-squad |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda scored his first goal of the season, the winning goal of a 2–1 home victory against [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]] on 4 February 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda winner claims points for Reds |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-winner-claims-points-for-reds |publisher=Adelaide United |date=4 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Sachapisani |title='Teachers from school came to watch me': Irankunda's all-time interview after stunning winner |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/irankunda-interview-shows-why-the-adelaide-teenager-is-so-special/ |website=keepup.com |date=4 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517070650/https://keepup.com.au/news/irankunda-interview-shows-why-the-adelaide-teenager-is-so-special/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His goal received praise from manager [[Carl Veart]] who stated, "This is the talent that Nestor has."<ref>{{cite web |title=Veart praises Irankunda after late winner |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-praises-irankunda-after-late-winner |publisher=Adelaide United |date=5 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517070653/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-praises-irankunda-after-late-winner |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Brissenden |first=Neve |title=Reds' Irankuda 'long way off' starting in ALM: coach |url=https://www.youngwitness.com.au/story/8081443/reds-irankuda-long-way-off-starting-in-alm-coach/ |website=The Young Witness |date=10 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Irankunda dedicated the goal to Spanish teammate and friend [[Juande]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda highlights necessity for improvement |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-highlights-necessity-for-improvement |publisher=Adelaide United |date=4 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064108/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-highlights-necessity-for-improvement/ |url-status=live }}</ref> who broke his leg in a 3–3 draw with [[Melbourne City FC|Melbourne City]] a week earlier.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/a-league/aleague-mens-melbourne-city-vs-adelaide-united-juande-breaks-leg-news-video-horror-injury-score-results/news-story/745d5dc87274dd8308ba3c48b61ff5fc|title=Horror injury stuns A-League as match paused for half-hour|website=[[Fox Sports (Australia)|FOX Sports]]|date=29 January 2023|access-date=23 August 2023|archive-date=8 October 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064448/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/a-league/aleague-mens-melbourne-city-vs-adelaide-united-juande-breaks-leg-news-video-horror-injury-score-results/news-story/745d5dc87274dd8308ba3c48b61ff5fc|url-status=live}}</ref> Irankunda furthered his reputation as a key player off the bench after scoring in three consecutive appearances for Adelaide United in the matches against Melbourne Victory (1–1),<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda saves Adelaide on Pride Cup day in Melbourne - High School Sports Video - ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/high-school/video/clip?id=35738220 |website=ESPN |date=26 February 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023}}</ref> Melbourne City (4–2),<ref>{{cite web |title=Veart's assessment of teen sensation Irankunda's dazzling cameo |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/teenage-star-irankunda-on-the-rise-for-adelaide-reds/ |website=keepup.com |date=3 March 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=18 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230518055039/https://keepup.com.au/news/teenage-star-irankunda-on-the-rise-for-adelaide-reds/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and Newcastle Jets (4–2).<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda credits fans for inspirational efforts |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-credits-fans-for-inspirational-efforts |publisher=Adelaide United |date=3 March 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517070650/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-credits-fans-for-inspirational-efforts |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Socceroos captain's advice for Nestory Irankunda after maiden Australia call-up |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/ryan-tells-irankunda-to-embrace-socceroos-call-up/ |website=keepup.com |date=14 March 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 |archive-date=18 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230518055042/https://keepup.com.au/news/ryan-tells-irankunda-to-embrace-socceroos-call-up/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He was awarded A-League Goal of the Month in February for his goal against Melbourne Victory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Isuzu UTE Goal of the Month February {{!}} Nestory Irankunda |url=https://keepup.com.au/videos/id/isuzu-ute-goal-of-the-month-february-nestory-irankunda/6322255495112/ |website=keepup.com |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=18 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230518055041/https://keepup.com.au/videos/id/isuzu-ute-goal-of-the-month-february-nestory-irankunda/6322255495112/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Irankunda was criticised in the media for his discipline issues when he started a brawl in the match against [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]] that led to Wanderers' captain [[Marcelo (footballer, born May 1987)|Marcelo]] getting sent-off for headlocking Irankunda after he provoked [[Calem Nieuwenhof]]. Another incident occurred on 23 April against [[Perth Glory FC|Perth Glory]] when he received a booking for kicking the broadcaster’s pitchside microphone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irate Irankunda needs to cool his fiery streak: Veart |url=https://www.cowraguardian.com.au/story/8144038/irate-irankunda-needs-to-cool-his-fiery-streak-veart/ |website=Cowra Guardian |date=31 March 2023 |access-date=17 May 2023 }}{{Dead link|date=August 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Watch: Adelaide young gun put in headlock as chaos erupts during wild all-in brawl |url=https://7news.com.au/sport/soccer/carl-veart-says-nestory-irankunda-needs-to-stay-calm-as-tempers-erupt-during-all-in-brawl-against-the-wanderers-c-10221009 |website=[[Seven News]] |date=1 April 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517104642/https://7news.com.au/sport/soccer/carl-veart-says-nestory-irankunda-needs-to-stay-calm-as-tempers-erupt-during-all-in-brawl-against-the-wanderers-c-10221009 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Matthewcomito |title=Unseen Irankunda moment explains why 'it's going to take time' to nurture prodigal talent |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-news-unseen-irankunda-moment-adelaide-united-perth-glory/ |website=keepup.com |date=23 April 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064518/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-news-unseen-irankunda-moment-adelaide-united-perth-glory/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the same match against Perth, Irankunda scored his fifth goal of the season in the 99th-minute of a 4–4 draw at the [[Perth Rectangular Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Glory, Adelaide slug it out in stunning ALM draw |url=https://thewest.com.au/sport/soccer/glory-adelaide-slug-it-out-in-high-scoring-alm-draw-c-10433816 |website=The West Australian |date=23 April 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=10 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230510210157/https://thewest.com.au/sport/soccer/glory-adelaide-slug-it-out-in-high-scoring-alm-draw-c-10433816 |url-status=live }}</ref> The goal brought his A-League career total to eight goals, surpassing Mohamed Toure's record as the competition’s highest under-18 goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Sachapisani |title=WATCH: The insane eight-goal draw that showcases one of the craziest ever seasons |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-victory-macarthur-perth-glory-adelaide-scores-goals-highlights-reaction-live-blog/ |website=keepup.com |date=23 April 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517123252/https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-victory-macarthur-perth-glory-adelaide-scores-goals-highlights-reaction-live-blog/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda was awarded the club's Rising Star accolade on 2 May.<ref>{{cite web |title=Holmes, Goodwin awarded Alagich, Vidmar Medals |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/holmes-goodwin-awarded-alagich-vidmar-medals |publisher=Adelaide United |date=2 May 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=6 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230506015043/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/holmes-goodwin-awarded-alagich-vidmar-medals |url-status=live }}</ref> He featured off the bench in United's final game of the season on 20 May where his side lost 2–0 against the eventual winners [[Central Coast Mariners FC|Central Coast Mariners]] at [[Central Coast Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |title=What Veart told devastated Irankunda in unseen pep talk after Semi Final heartbreak |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-a-league-news-adelaide-united-carl-veart-craig-goodwin/ |website=keepup.com |date=25 May 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=25 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230525040607/https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-a-league-news-adelaide-united-carl-veart-craig-goodwin/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Mariners eye Grand Final berth after successfully nullifying Irankunda |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/37674854/central-coast-mariners-eye-grand-final-berth-successfully-nullifying-nestory-irankunda |website=ESPN |publisher=Australia Correspondent |date=14 May 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064450/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/37674854/central-coast-mariners-eye-grand-final-berth-successfully-nullifying-nestory-irankunda |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Harrington |first=Anna |title=Adelaide ponder Irankunda start for Mariners final |url=https://thewest.com.au/sport/soccer/adelaide-ponder-irankunda-start-for-mariners-final-c-10701322 |website=The West Australian |date=19 May 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023}}</ref>

====2023–24: Final season with Adelaide United====
During [[2023–24 Adelaide United FC season#Pre-season|Adelaide's 2023–24 pre-season]], Irankunda returned to [[Adelaide United FC Youth|Adelaide United Youth]], where he scored the winner in the Young Reds' 4–3 [[2023 Football South Australia season#Finals|elimination final]] victory against [[Adelaide Comets FC|Adelaide Comets]] in August 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=Finals and Desire: Young Reds march on |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/finals-and-desire-young-reds-march-on |publisher=Adelaide United |date=24 August 2023 |access-date=26 August 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064451/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/finals-and-desire-young-reds-march-on/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the final minutes of the semi-final against [[Campbelltown City SC|Campbeltown City]], hecollapsed to the ground and had difficulty breathing after hitting his head whilst attempting to make a pass. Christian Verdicchio, who was one of the match officials present, promptly aided him to ensure he would be able to breathe. Irankunda was soon taken off the field and monitored before reporting to training the following day.<ref>{{cite web |title=Heroic ref to the rescue as Adelaide player swallows tongue |url=https://www.9news.com.au/national/heroic-referee-saves-day-after-nestory-irankunda-swallows-tongue/c64c6daa-4e81-4adc-85ca-3e1c3f813dd3 |website=9News |date=26 August 2023 |access-date=26 August 2023 |archive-date=26 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230826143250/https://www.9news.com.au/national/heroic-referee-saves-day-after-nestory-irankunda-swallows-tongue/c64c6daa-4e81-4adc-85ca-3e1c3f813dd3 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Leah |title=Nestory Irankunda saved after a bad fall by match official Dr Christian Verdicchio |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/nestory-irankunda-saved-after-a-bad-fall-by-match-official-dr-christian-verdicchio/news-story/6171e89ca0fd596b4afa7a5cce2b6f69?amp&nk=d0a648aca6a130f3c0f8bfd302943754-1693059082 |website=Adelaide Now |publisher=The Advertiser |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230826141113/https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/nestory-irankunda-saved-after-a-bad-fall-by-match-official-dr-christian-verdicchio/news-story/6171e89ca0fd596b4afa7a5cce2b6f69?amp&nk=d0a648aca6a130f3c0f8bfd302943754-1693059082 |archive-date=26 August 2023 |date=26 August 2023 |access-date=26 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Cornthwaite |first=Rob |title=Socceroos young gun's life saved by quick-thinking referee |url=https://7news.com.au/sport/soccer/socceroos-young-gun-nestory-irankundas-life-saved-by-referee-who-happened-to-be-a-doctor-c-11716470 |website=Seven News |access-date=28 August 2023 |date=26 August 2023 |archive-date=28 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230828020809/https://7news.com.au/sport/soccer/socceroos-young-gun-nestory-irankundas-life-saved-by-referee-who-happened-to-be-a-doctor-c-11716470 |url-status=live }}</ref> As cautioned by the doctor, he missed the [[2023 Australia Cup#Round of 16|Round of 16]] clash against Western Sydney Wanderers at [[Marconi Stadium]],<ref>{{cite web |title='Something didn't look right': The referee who rushed to the rescue of an A-League star |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-28/soccer-referee-on-nestory-irankunda-choking-emergency/102784704 |website=ABC News |date=28 August 2023 |access-date=29 August 2023 |archive-date=29 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230829014304/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-08-28/soccer-referee-on-nestory-irankunda-choking-emergency/102784704 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Veart expects 'entertaining' Wanderers Cup clash |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-expects-entertaining-wanderers-cup-clash |publisher=Adelaide United |date=28 August 2023 |access-date=29 August 2023 |archive-date=9 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230909030932/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-expects-entertaining-wanderers-cup-clash |url-status=live }}</ref> and subsequently, the semi final second leg against Campbelltown.<ref>{{cite web |last=D'Urbano |first=Nick |title=Adelaide's youngsters achieve stunning first after 17 minute semi-final blitz |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/adelaide-united-npl-south-australia-grand-final-modbury-jets/ |website=keepup.com |access-date=6 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230906204714/https://keepup.com.au/news/adelaide-united-npl-south-australia-grand-final-modbury-jets/ |archive-date=6 September 2023 |date=3 September 2023 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Prior to his injury, Irankunda made one appearance for the first-team in the [[2023 Australia Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=United progress to Australia Cup Round of 16 |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/united-progress-to-australia-cup-round-of-16 |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=15 October 2023 |date=14 August 2023 |archive-date=20 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231020171923/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/united-progress-to-australia-cup-round-of-16 |url-status=live }}</ref> After 35 substitute appearances, he made his starting debut for Adelaide United on 20 October in a 3–0 victory over Central Coast Mariners at home.<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Mariners' title defence begins with defeat as rampant Reds usher in new era in style |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-3-0-central-coast-mariners-match-report-goals-highlights/ |publisher=[[A-League]] |access-date=20 October 2023 |date=20 October 2023 |archive-date=20 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231020160302/https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-3-0-central-coast-mariners-match-report-goals-highlights/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Reid |first=Harrison |title=Socceroos young gun makes extraordinary recovery after pitch collapse |url=https://7news.com.au/sport/a-league/socceroos-young-gun-nestory-irankunda-makes-a-league-appearance-after-having-life-saved-in-august-c-12275046 |publisher=Seven News |access-date=21 October 2023 |date=21 October 2023 |archive-date=21 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231021005411/https://7news.com.au/sport/a-league/socceroos-young-gun-nestory-irankunda-makes-a-league-appearance-after-having-life-saved-in-august-c-12275046 |url-status=live }}</ref> 

Irankunda scored his first goal as a starter (and for the season) on 29 October from a free-kick in a 6–0 victory over Melbourne City at [[Coopers Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |last=D'Urbano |first=Nick |title=Irankunda's praise for fellow Reds youngsters after 19-minute blitz of Melbourne City |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/irankunda-free-kick-goal-adelaide-melbourne-city-a-league-men/ |publisher=A-League |access-date=29 October 2023 |date=29 October 2023 |archive-date=29 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029212750/https://aleagues.com.au/news/irankunda-free-kick-goal-adelaide-melbourne-city-a-league-men/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Gagliardi |first=Lee |title=Irankunda and fellow teens lead the way for super Reds |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8404443/irankunda-and-fellow-teens-lead-the-way-for-super-reds/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=29 October 2023 |date=29 October 2023 |archive-date=29 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029212750/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8404443/irankunda-and-fellow-teens-lead-the-way-for-super-reds/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 4 November, he was sent off in an Original Rivalry match against Melbourne Victory after receiving two bookings.<ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Nestory Irankunda and the unbearable weight of expectation on young shoulders |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/nov/07/nestory-irankunda-and-the-unbearable-weight-of-expectation-on-young-shoulders |website=The Guardian |access-date=8 November 2023 |date=7 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064451/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/nov/07/nestory-irankunda-and-the-unbearable-weight-of-expectation-on-young-shoulders |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Victory, Reds play out spiteful ALM draw |url=https://thewest.com.au/sport/soccer/victory-reds-play-out-spiteful-alm-draw-c-12440631 |website=The West Australian |access-date=4 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231104115937/https://thewest.com.au/sport/soccer/victory-reds-play-out-spiteful-alm-draw-c-12440631 |archive-date=4 November 2023 |date=4 November 2023}}</ref> He missed the following league game against [[Sydney FC]] as a result.<ref>{{cite web |title=Veart: It's a big game and hopefully we can get lots of supporters get behind us |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-its-a-big-game-and-hopefully-we-can-get-lots-of-supporters-get-behind-us |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=10 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023 |archive-date=10 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110095840/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-its-a-big-game-and-hopefully-we-can-get-lots-of-supporters-get-behind-us |url-status=live }}</ref> He was later awarded the October nomination for [[A-League Men Young Footballer of the Year|Young Footballer of the Year]] for his preceding performances.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda earns Young Footballer of the Year nomination for October |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-adelaide-united-young-footballer-of-year-october/ |publisher=[[A-League]] |access-date=14 November 2023 |date=13 November 2023 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231114015649/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-adelaide-united-young-footballer-of-year-october/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After the announcement of his move to Bayern,<ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Introducing Bayern Munich's next prodigy: Nestory Irankunda |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/38954161/bayern-munich-next-prodigy-nestory-irankunda |website=ESPN |access-date=26 November 2023 |date=22 November 2023 |archive-date=26 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231126203920/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/38954161/bayern-munich-next-prodigy-nestory-irankunda |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Larkin |first=Steve |title=Irankunda's ALM farewell tour opens against Western Utd |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/irankundas-alm-farewell-tour-opens-against-western-utd-602772 |website=FTBL |access-date=26 November 2023 |date=25 November 2023 |archive-date=25 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231125102956/https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/irankundas-alm-farewell-tour-opens-against-western-utd-602772 |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda returned from suspension on 26 November against [[Western United FC|Western United]], managing one assist to [[Ben Halloran]] in a 3–1 win at [[Eureka Stadium]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Adelaide bounce back from Sydney trouncing with win over Western on the road |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/adelaide-bounce-back-from-sydney-trouncing-with-with-win-over-western-on-the-road |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=26 November 2023 |date=26 November 2023 |archive-date=26 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231126113325/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/adelaide-bounce-back-from-sydney-trouncing-with-with-win-over-western-on-the-road |url-status=live }}</ref> and later accumulating two assists in his next three league matches.<ref name=soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Adelaide bounce back from Sydney trouncing with with[sic] win over Western on the road |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/adelaide-bounce-back-from-sydney-trouncing-with-with-win-over-western-on-the-road |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=22 December 2023 |date=26 November 2023 |archive-date=26 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231126203924/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/adelaide-bounce-back-from-sydney-trouncing-with-with-win-over-western-on-the-road |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Reds lose in Seven-goal thriller |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/reds-lose-in-seven-goal-thriller |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=22 December 2023 |date=4 December 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064555/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/reds-lose-in-seven-goal-thriller/ |url-status=live }}</ref> 

Irankunda eventually returned to the starting line-up after two further substitute appearances on 4 January 2024, being named against Wellington Phoenix at home.<ref name="5/1/2024">{{cite web |last=Gagliardi |first=Lee |title=Bayern-bound Irankunda back to his best for Adelaide |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/bayern-bound-irankunda-back-to-his-best-for-adelaide-603777 |website=FTBL |access-date=7 January 2024 |date=5 January 2024 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107111318/https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/bayern-bound-irankunda-back-to-his-best-for-adelaide-603777 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="aleague-5/1/24">{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=Carl Veart wanted a response from an Adelaide teenager and he got it |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-adelaide-united-carl-veart-wellington-phoenix-press-conference-highlights-goals-a-league/ |website=A-League |access-date=7 January 2024 |date=5 January 2024 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107111318/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-adelaide-united-carl-veart-wellington-phoenix-press-conference-highlights-goals-a-league/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda contributed towards Adelaide's two goals, including an assist to [[Hiroshi Ibusuki]], in a 2–2 draw by full-time.<ref name="5/1/2024"/><ref name="aleague-5/1/24"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Lethal Phoenix star keeps scoring streak alive as Reds striker answers back in entertaining draw |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/lethal-phoenix-star-keeps-scoring-streak-alive-as-reds-striker-answers-back-in-entertaining-draw |website=Adelaide United |access-date=7 January 2024 |date=4 January 2024 |archive-date=7 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107111317/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/lethal-phoenix-star-keeps-scoring-streak-alive-as-reds-striker-answers-back-in-entertaining-draw |url-status=live }}</ref> In particular, Ibusuki acted as a mentor for Irankunda,<ref>{{cite web |last=Harper |first=Lachlan |title=How 195cm giant landed in a place he didn't know |url=https://wwos.nine.com.au/football/a-league-news-2024-hiroshi-ibusuki-career-exclusive-adelaide-united-unite-round/c278c616-42b6-4280-8fbe-1bbe36a436e0 |publisher=[[Nine News]] |access-date=13 January 2024 |date=11 January 2024 |archive-date=13 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240113015614/https://wwos.nine.com.au/football/a-league-news-2024-hiroshi-ibusuki-career-exclusive-adelaide-united-unite-round/c278c616-42b6-4280-8fbe-1bbe36a436e0 |url-status=live }}</ref> forming a partnership which saw them both score against Sydney FC in a 4–3 victory at [[Sydney Football Stadium (2022)|Allianz Stadium]] on 14 January; Irankunda scored once and his second of the season, assisted by Ibusuki who scored a [[hat-trick]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Godfrey |first=Dan |title=Sky Blues Comeback Not Enough |url=https://sydneyfc.com/news/sky-blues-comeback-not-enough |publisher=[[Sydney FC]] |access-date=13 January 2024 |date=13 January 2024 |archive-date=13 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240113122726/https://sydneyfc.com/news/sky-blues-comeback-not-enough |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 February, Irankunda made his 50th league appearance off the bench in a 3–3 draw against Perth Glory at home, becoming the youngest player, aged exactly 18, to reach this milestone and overtaking [[Liberato Cacace]]'s record of 19 years, 5 months, 10 days old.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=Irankunda set to smash A-Leagues record this weekend: This is the list he'll top by a mile |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-men-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-cacace-farrell-mariners/ |website=A-Leagues |date=6 February 2024 |access-date=10 February 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065104/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-men-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-cacace-farrell-mariners/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In the post-match conference, Irankunda was criticised by Veart for not meeting to club standard, adding he hasn't "seen enough happiness from him."<ref>{{cite web |last=Migliaccio |first=Val |title='Don't see enough happiness': Adelaide boss' sad reveal amid Bayern-bound teen's struggles |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/dont-see-enough-happiness-adelaide-boss-sad-reveal-amid-bayernbound-teens-struggles/news-story/8ec7303bacbe5c18ad0ff5db3856e890 |website=Fox Sports |publisher=NCA NewsWire |access-date=16 February 2024 |date=10 February 2024 |archive-date=16 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240216234804/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/dont-see-enough-happiness-adelaide-boss-sad-reveal-amid-bayernbound-teens-struggles/news-story/8ec7303bacbe5c18ad0ff5db3856e890 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=Adelaide coach's honest view on Reds sensation: 'In this country we make it very difficult...' |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-veart-bayern-munich-news/ |website=A-Leagues |access-date=16 February 2024 |date=10 February 2024 |archive-date=16 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240216233300/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-veart-bayern-munich-news/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Campo |first=Jose |title=Irankunda's journey hits spiralling pressure as he navigates increasing demands |url=https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/navigating-the-demands-irankunda-s-journey-amidst-spiralling-pressure |website=Front Page Football |access-date=16 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240216233201/https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/navigating-the-demands-irankunda-s-journey-amidst-spiralling-pressure |archive-date=16 February 2024 |date=16 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Monteverde |first=Marco |title=Adelaide United intent on taking Nestory Irankunda to the 'next level' |url=https://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/football/adelaide-united-intent-on-taking-nestory-irankunda-to-the-next-level/news-story/297dbcf40b44e62bdb524daa750b3a9b |website=Herald Sun |publisher=NCA NewsWire |access-date=16 February 2024 |date=16 February 2024 |archive-date=17 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240217015429/https://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/football/adelaide-united-intent-on-taking-nestory-irankunda-to-the-next-level/news-story/297dbcf40b44e62bdb524daa750b3a9b |url-status=live }}</ref> On 9 March, Irankunda scored his third goal of the campaign and the equaliser in a 2–1 home defeat to Melbourne Victory.<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Golden Boot leader answers 'the million dollar question' following him through mini drought |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-melbourne-victory-match-report-goals-highlights-irankunda-fornaroli/ |website=A-League |access-date=10 March 2024 |date=9 March 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064955/https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-melbourne-victory-match-report-goals-highlights-irankunda-fornaroli/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 29 March, Irankunda scored his first professional hat-trick in a 4–1 home win over Western United.<ref>{{cite web |last=Gagliardi |first=Lee |title=Irankunda nets hat-trick in Reds' 4-1 win over Western |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8573884/irankunda-nets-hat-trick-in-reds-4-1-win-over-western/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=29 March 2024 |archive-date=30 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240330001033/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8573884/irankunda-nets-hat-trick-in-reds-4-1-win-over-western/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Aged 18 years and 49 days, he became the youngest player to score a hat-trick in the A-League Men and the second youngest to do so in Australian men's football history.<ref>{{cite web |title=History for Irankunda! Bayern-bound teen's first career hat-trick smashes records in big win for Reds |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/history-for-irankunda-bayern-bound-teens-first-career-hat-trick-smashes-records-in-big-win-for-reds/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=29 March 2024 |archive-date=30 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240330001032/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/history-for-irankunda-bayern-bound-teens-first-career-hat-trick-smashes-records-in-big-win-for-reds/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Adelaide's 'very rare talent' continues rapid rise as historic hat-trick blows everyone away |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-hat-trick-adelaide-united-bayern-munich-goals-highlights-western-united-match-report/ |publisher=A-League |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=29 March 2024 |archive-date=2 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402005605/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-hat-trick-adelaide-united-bayern-munich-goals-highlights-western-united-match-report/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='There's a lot of expectation on him': Teen A-League sensation shakes off 'challenging' year with record-breaking hat-trick |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2024-03-30/nestory-irankunda-scores-youngest-a-league-men-hat-trick/103650946 |website=ABC News |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=29 March 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064956/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2024-03-30/nestory-irankunda-scores-youngest-a-league-men-hat-trick/103650946 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 8 April, in the following match, Irankunda provided two assists in a 4–2 comeback win against Perth Glory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Incredible attacking display sees Adelaide seal stunning come-from-behind win over Perth Glory |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/incredible-attacking-display-sees-adelaide-seal-stunning-come-from-behind-win-over-perth-glory/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=7 April 2024 |date=7 April 2024 |archive-date=7 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240407094806/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/incredible-attacking-display-sees-adelaide-seal-stunning-come-from-behind-win-over-perth-glory/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Ibusuki, Irankunda lift Reds to ALM win over Glory |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8583200/ibusuki-irankunda-lift-reds-to-alm-win-over-glory/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=7 April 2024 |date=7 April 2024 |archive-date=7 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240407215726/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8583200/ibusuki-irankunda-lift-reds-to-alm-win-over-glory/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He played his last match at home on 12 April, scoring a long-range goal, in a 2–1 defeat to [[Macarthur FC]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Ten-man Bulls spoil Irankunda's farewell party in shock comeback after second-half send-off |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/ten-man-bulls-spoil-irankundas-farewell-party-in-shock-comeback-after-second-half-send-off/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=13 April 2024 |date=12 April 2024 |archive-date=12 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240412121616/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/ten-man-bulls-spoil-irankundas-farewell-party-in-shock-comeback-after-second-half-send-off/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He added a goal to his tally in a 3–3 draw against Western United on 16 April.<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Dramatic end to 6-goal thriller as Western put big dent in ends Reds' finals hopes in stoppage time |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/dramatic-end-to-6-goal-thriller-as-western-put-big-dent-in-ends-reds-finals-hopes-in-stoppage-time/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=24 April 2024 |date=16 April 2024 |archive-date=24 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240424061746/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/dramatic-end-to-6-goal-thriller-as-western-put-big-dent-in-ends-reds-finals-hopes-in-stoppage-time/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In late-April, Irankunda was announced in the [[2024 A-Leagues All Stars Men game|2024 A-League Men All Stars squad]] that was set to play against [[Premier League]] club [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda one of FOUR A-League All Stars named as iconic Kappa playing kit unveiled |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-one-of-four-a-league-all-stars-named-as-iconic-kappa-playing-kit-unveiled/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=24 April 2024 |date=23 April 2024 |archive-date=23 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240423231553/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-one-of-four-a-league-all-stars-named-as-iconic-kappa-playing-kit-unveiled/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda played his last match on 1 May for Adelaide United in a 2–0 away lost to Central Coast Mariners, allowing the Mariners to win the [[2023–24 A-League Men|premiership title]] over runners-up Wellington Phoenix on the final matchday.<ref>{{cite web |title=Reds survive late Roar onslaught to edge seven-goal thriller |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/premiers-central-coast-crush-phoenix-dreams-end-12-year-wait-with-final-day-win/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=2 May 2024 |date=1 May 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064956/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/premiers-central-coast-crush-phoenix-dreams-end-12-year-wait-with-final-day-win/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Veart backs Irankunda to make an impression at Bayern |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8613700/veart-backs-irankunda-to-make-an-impression-at-bayern/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=2 May 2024 |date=1 May 2024 |archive-date=2 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502072845/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8613700/veart-backs-irankunda-to-make-an-impression-at-bayern/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda departed with 16 goals in 60 league appearance, in total, for Adelaide United.<ref>{{cite web |title=Every word of Nestory Irankunda's beautiful A-Leagues farewell interview |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-last-game-interview-bayern-munich-video-highlights-adelaide-united/ |publisher=A-League |access-date=2 May 2024 |date=1 May 2024 |archive-date=2 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240502072845/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-last-game-interview-bayern-munich-video-highlights-adelaide-united/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He was named the [[A-League Men Young Footballer of the Year]], jointly with [[Alex Paulsen]], at the end of the season.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Every Isuzu UTE A-League award winner: Johnny Warren Medalist, Goal of the Year & more |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-award-winners-2023-24-full-list-details/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=9 June 2024 |date=25 May 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065108/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-award-winners-2023-24-full-list-details/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Bayern Munich ===
On 14 November 2023, Adelaide United announced the sale of Irankunda to Bayern Munich for a club-record fee, with the forward set to join the club on 1 July 2024.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda Seals Bayern Move |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-seals-bayern-move |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=14 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231114094428/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-seals-bayern-move |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=FC Bayern sign Australian talent Nestory Irankunda |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/11/fc-bayern-sign-australian-talent-nestory-irankunda |publisher=[[FC Bayern Munich|FC Bayern]] |access-date=14 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231114110552/https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2023/11/fc-bayern-sign-australian-talent-nestory-irankunda |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda secures Bayern Munich move |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-secures-european-move |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=14 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231114110551/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-secures-european-move |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |agency=Australian Associated Press |title='Dream come true': wonderkid Nestory Irankunda signs for Bayern Munich |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/nov/14/dream-come-true-wonderkid-irankunda-signs-for-bayern-munich |website=The Guardian |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065110/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/nov/14/dream-come-true-wonderkid-irankunda-signs-for-bayern-munich |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Fabrizio Romano]] reported four days prior that Bayern Munich submitted an offer for Irankunda worth £3 million with add-ons, potentially breaking the league transfer record set by [[Marco Tilio]] in his move to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Michell |first=Tim |title=Nestory Irankunda on cusp of move to German football heavyweights Bayern Munich |url=https://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/football/on-the-attack-robbie-slater-and-marco-monteverde-on-the-aleagues-biggest-issues/news-story/6a29f3399aa9c9401367da4cdcded4a4?amp&nk=018e5c3b5c15cadb4735b08484ae1b6b-1699612254 |website=Herald Sun |publisher=Code Sports |access-date=10 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231110103045/https://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/football/on-the-attack-robbie-slater-and-marco-monteverde-on-the-aleagues-biggest-issues/news-story/6a29f3399aa9c9401367da4cdcded4a4?amp&nk=018e5c3b5c15cadb4735b08484ae1b6b-1699612254 |archive-date=10 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Mansell |first=Jackson |title=BREAKING: Bayern Munich set to offer record transfer fee for Nestory Irankunda |url=https://www.theinnersanctum.com.au/breaking-bayern-munich-set-to-offer-record-transfer-fee-for-nestory-irankunda/ |website=The Inner Sanctum |access-date=10 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023 |archive-date=10 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110085237/https://www.theinnersanctum.com.au/breaking-bayern-munich-set-to-offer-record-transfer-fee-for-nestory-irankunda/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Waterworth |first=Ben |title=17yo Aussie sensation Nestory Irankunda on verge of signing mega deal with Euro giants |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/transfers/football-transfer-news-2023-nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-contract-adelaide-united-star-on-verge-of-bombshell-deal/news-story/fd33130bf68233275442a76e0d7afd91 |website=Fox Sports |access-date=10 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008064958/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/transfers/football-transfer-news-2023-nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-contract-adelaide-united-star-on-verge-of-bombshell-deal/news-story/fd33130bf68233275442a76e0d7afd91 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Irankunda to Bayern? Famous transfer guru drops biggest hint yet & hints at eye-watering fee! |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-fabrizio-romano-17-adelaide-united-aleague-men-transfer-latest/ |website=keepup.com |access-date=10 November 2023 |date=10 November 2023 |archive-date=10 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231110105311/https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-fabrizio-romano-17-adelaide-united-aleague-men-transfer-latest/ |url-status=live }}</ref> It has also been reported by other outlets that Bayern submitted an initial offer of €750,000 with a final payment potentially rising to over €3 million if agreed conditions are met.<ref>{{cite web |last=McGuire |first=Michael |title=Adelaide United's Nestory Irankunda to live out his dreams and those of his father with Bayern Munich deal |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-to-live-out-his-dreams-and-those-of-his-father-with-bayern-munich-deal/news-story/0f6d32ae0cba3fe342f7038ab8144bfc?amp&nk=9f5ef1e0f32c86c5ba1d364c48db820d-1700011992 |website=Adelaide Now |publisher=The Advertiser |access-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231115013255/https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/adelaide-uniteds-nestory-irankunda-to-live-out-his-dreams-and-those-of-his-father-with-bayern-munich-deal/news-story/0f6d32ae0cba3fe342f7038ab8144bfc?amp&nk=9f5ef1e0f32c86c5ba1d364c48db820d-1700011992 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |date=15 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Linner |first1=Nico |last2=Verhoff |first2=David |last3=Altschäffl |first3=Tobias |title=FC Bayern: Vor Nestory Irankunda! Welche Auslands-Talente der Klub schon holte! |url=https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/bayern-muenchen/fc-bayern-vor-nestory-irankunda-welche-auslands-talente-der-klub-schon-holte-86097968.bild.html |website=bild.de |access-date=15 November 2023 |language=de |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231114230937/https://www.bild.de/sport/fussball/bayern-muenchen/fc-bayern-vor-nestory-irankunda-welche-auslands-talente-der-klub-schon-holte-86097968.bild.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Verwirrung um Irankunda-Deal des FC Bayern |url=https://www.sport.de/news/ne5831843/fc-bayern-schnaeppchen-millionen-abloese-verwirrung-um-irankunda-deal/ |website=sport.de |access-date=15 November 2023 |language=de |date=14 November 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115070220/https://www.sport.de/news/ne5831843/fc-bayern-schnaeppchen-millionen-abloese-verwirrung-um-irankunda-deal/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Irankunda arrived at [[FC Bayern Campus|Bayern Campus]] on 18 June and was set to train with [[FC Bayern Munich II|Bayern Munich II]] before [[2024–25 FC Bayern Munich season|preseason]] began in [[Waidring]] on 21 June.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda im Training der Amateure am Ball |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2024/06/nestory-irankunda-legt-bei-den-amateuren-los |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |access-date=19 June 2024 |language=de |date=18 June 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065021/https://fcbayern.com/profis-assets/keycloak-init.html?debug=false&url=https%3A%2F%2Fid.fcbayern.com%2Fauth&realm=fcbayern&client_id=website&scope=bpid&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffcbayern.com%2Fde%2F500 |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his non-competitive debut for the reserve team on 6 July and scored his side's only goal in a 2–1 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] defeat to [[SC Austria Lustenau|Austria Lustenau]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Amateure müssen sich Lustenau knapp geschlagen geben |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/spielberichte/2024/07/spielbericht-austria-lustenau-fc-bayern-amateure |publisher=FC Bayern |access-date=8 July 2024 |language=de |date=6 July 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065515/https://fcbayern.com/profis-assets/keycloak-init.html?debug=false&url=https%3A%2F%2Fid.fcbayern.com%2Fauth&realm=fcbayern&client_id=website&scope=bpid&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffcbayern.com%2Fde%2F500 |url-status=live }}</ref> In mid-July, Irankunda began training with the first-team under manager [[Vincent Kompany]].<ref>{{cite web |title=FC Bayern erstmals mit Coach Kompany auf dem Trainingsplatz |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2024/07/erste-eindruecke-fc-bayern-erstmals-mit-coach-kompany-auf-dem-trainingsplatz |publisher=FC Bayern |access-date=20 July 2024 |language=de |date=18 July 2024 |archive-date=21 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240721202337/https://fcbayern.com/de/news/2024/07/erste-eindruecke-fc-bayern-erstmals-mit-coach-kompany-auf-dem-trainingsplatz |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 July, he made his competitive debut for the reserve team in the [[Regionalliga Bayern]], winning 1–0 against [[SV Wacker Burghausen|Wacker Burghausen]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Amateure jubeln zum Regionalliga-Auftakt in Burghausen |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/amateure/regionalliga-bayern/2024-2025/sv-wacker-burghausen-fc-bayern-amateure-18-07-2024/spielbericht |publisher=FC Bayern |access-date=20 July 2024 |language=de |date=19 July 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065627/https://fcbayern.com/profis-assets/keycloak-init.html?debug=false&url=https%3A%2F%2Fid.fcbayern.com%2Fauth&realm=fcbayern&client_id=website&scope=bpid&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffcbayern.com%2Fde%2F500 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Knaller-Start für Bayern-Juwel! |url=https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/regionalliga-bayern/2024/07/knaller-start-fur-bayern-juwel |website=SPORT1 |access-date=20 July 2024 |language=de |date=18 July 2024 |archive-date=19 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240719164501/https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/regionalliga-bayern/2024/07/knaller-start-fur-bayern-juwel |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda made his non-competitive debut for the first-team six days later, registering an assist and goal in a 14–1 friendly win against [[FC Rottach-Egern]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Goals galore in Bayern's opening friendly |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/friendly/2024-2025/testspiel-fc-rottach-egern-fc-bayern-24-07-2024/report |access-date=27 July 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065516/https://fcbayern.com/profis-assets/keycloak-init.html?debug=false&url=https%3A%2F%2Fid.fcbayern.com%2Fauth&realm=fcbayern&client_id=website&scope=bpid&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffcbayern.com%2Fen%2F500 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda scores in Bayern Munich pre-season friendly |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-scores-bayern-munich-pre-season-friendly |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=27 July 2024 |date=25 July 2024 |archive-date=27 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240727070319/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-scores-bayern-munich-pre-season-friendly |url-status=live }}</ref> On 31 July, he was announced to be included in the pre-season squad that was set to tour [[Seoul]], South Korea to play [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=A-Leagues reunion awaits as two Aussies named for big Bayern trip to face Ange's Spurs |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-squad-to-play-ange-postecoglou-tottenham-pavlesic-bundesliga-news-a-league-aussies-abroad-socceroos/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=1 August 2024 |date=31 July 2024 |archive-date=1 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240801084551/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-bayern-munich-squad-to-play-ange-postecoglou-tottenham-pavlesic-bundesliga-news-a-league-aussies-abroad-socceroos/ |url-status=live }}</ref> who were managed by fellow Australian [[Ange Postecoglou]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Socceroos Abroad: Scottish Premiership starts, Yazbek debuts, Irankunda vs Postecoglou |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/socceroos-abroad-scottish-premiership-starts-yazbek-debuts-irankunda-vs-postecoglou |publisher=Socceroos |access-date=8 August 2024 |date=2 August 2024 |archive-date=8 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240808164031/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/socceroos-abroad-scottish-premiership-starts-yazbek-debuts-irankunda-vs-postecoglou |url-status=live }}</ref> After his first month in Bayern, Irankunda was praised by Kompany for his performances in preseason and with the first-team, despite being a new signing to a foreign club, earning him a spot on the bench in the [[DFB-Pokal]] match against [[SSV Ulm 1846|SSV Ulm]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Irankunda's Bayern start delights Australia boss |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/40935890/nestory-irankunda-bayern-form-delights-australia-boss-graham-arnold |website=ESPN |access-date=22 August 2024 |date=21 August 2024 |archive-date=22 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240822001832/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/40935890/nestory-irankunda-bayern-form-delights-australia-boss-graham-arnold |url-status=live }}</ref> Returning to the reserve team, Irankunda was named [[man of the match]] after scoring a brace and his first competitive goal for the club in a 4–1 win against [[FC Würzburger Kickers|Würzburger Kickers]] on 24 August.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ungeschlagen-Serie hält an: Amateure siegen deutlich in Würzburg |url=https://fcbayern.com/de/spiele/amateure/regionalliga-bayern/2024-2025/fc-wuerzburger-kickers-fc-bayern-amateure-23-08-2024/spielbericht |publisher=FC Bayern |access-date=25 August 2024 |language=de |date=24 August 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065517/https://fcbayern.com/profis-assets/keycloak-init.html?debug=false&url=https%3A%2F%2Fid.fcbayern.com%2Fauth&realm=fcbayern&client_id=website&scope=bpid&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Ffcbayern.com%2Fde%2F500 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 December 2024, he received his second call-up with the Bayern Munich senior team for a 5–1 away win [[UEFA Champions League]] match against Ukrainian club [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]], as an unused substitute however.<ref>https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2042011--shakhtar-vs-bayern-munchen/</ref> Irankunda also played three matches and scored one goal for the Bayern Munich [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|youth team]] in the [[UEFA Youth League]].<ref>https://onefootball.com/en/match/2551139</ref><ref>https://onefootball.com/en/match/2551147</ref>

====Loan to Grasshopper====
On 4 January 2025, he joined Swiss record champions [[Grasshopper Club Zurich|Grasshopper]] for a six-month loan until 30 June.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |url=https://www.gcz.ch/en/news/article/1/bayern-youngster-nestory-irankunda-signs-for-gc-zurich/|title=Bayern youngster Nestory Irankunda signs for GC Zurich |date=4 January 2025|access-date=4 January 2025}}</ref> After four matches for the club, Irankunda provided his first assist in a draw against [[Lausanne-Sport]] in the [[Swiss Super League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bluewin.ch/en/sport/football/gc-have-to-settle-for-a-point-despite-mucis-overhead-kick-2546414.html |title=GC have to settle for a point despite Muci's overhead kick|first=Syd|last=Battistuzzi|date=4 February 2025|website=bluewin.ch}}</ref> Another assist came in the following match against [[FC Lugano|Lugano]], but Irankunda was substituted off with an injury in the 36th minute of that match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/socceroos-abroad-goodwin-and-irankunda-notch-assists|first=Tim|last=Gibson|date=10 February 2025 |title=Socceroos Abroad: Goodwin and Irankunda notch assists}}</ref> Following a third assist in four games on 22 February, in a 2–2 draw away to [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne]], he was chosen by the fans as player of the month for February.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |url=https://www.gcz.ch/en/news/article/1/nestory-irankunda-is-player-of-the-month-february/|title=Nestory Irankunda is the Player of the Month February |date=27 February 2025|access-date=27 February 2025}}</ref> He returned to Munich at the end of the season.<ref name="departures">{{cite web |title=GC Zürich verabschiedet mehrere Spieler |url=https://www.gcz.ch/news/artikel/1/gc-zuerich-verabschiedet-mehrere-spieler/ |publisher=[[Grasshopper Club Zurich]] |access-date=17 June 2025 |date=17 June 2025}}</ref>

===Watford===
On 18 July 2025, Irankunda signed a five-year contract with [[EFL Championship]] side [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.watfordfc.com/news/2025/july/18/official-welcome-irankunda/ |title=Official: Welcome Irankunda |publisher=Watford F.C. |date=18 July 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jul/19/socceroos-star-nestory-irankunda-signs-five-year-deal-with-watford-in-move-to-championship |title=Socceroos star Nestory Irankunda signs five-year deal with Watford in move to Championship |work=The Guardian |date=19 July 2025 }}</ref> On 24 August 2025, Irankunda scored his first goal for Watford, netting a 25-yard free kick in a 1–1 Championship draw away to [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Press |first=Australian Associated |date=2025-08-24 |title=Socceroos star Nestory Irankunda scores first goal for Watford with stunning free kick |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/aug/24/socceroos-star-nestory-irankunda-scores-first-goal-for-watford-with-stunning-free-kick |access-date=2026-02-02 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

== International career ==
=== Youth ===
Eligible to represent [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]], [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]], or [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Who is Nestory Irankunda? Australia's latest football sensation set to take Socceroos by storm |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/au/football/news/nestory-irankunda-australia-socceroos-adelaide-united/exdjhnev6adicmw3ezythdbq |website=Sporting News |date=20 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=16 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230516123354/https://www.sportingnews.com/au/football/news/nestory-irankunda-australia-socceroos-adelaide-united/exdjhnev6adicmw3ezythdbq |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda received his first international call-up in September 2022 from [[Football Australia|Australia]] to represent the [[Australia men's national under-17 soccer team|under-17 side]] in the [[2023 AFC U-17 Asian Cup qualification]] matches.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda, Phillis, Talladira selected for Joeys Camp |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-phillis-talladira-selected-for-joeys-camp |publisher=Adelaide United |date=12 September 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517123250/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-phillis-talladira-selected-for-joeys-camp |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut against the [[Northern Mariana Islands national under-18 football team|Northern Mariana Islands]], netting a [[hat-trick]] by the 38th-minute before scoring two more goals to complete a 23–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |title=Subway Joeys comfortably defeat Northern Mariana Islands in Shepparton opener |url=https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-comfortably-defeat-north-mariana-islands-shepparton-opener |publisher=Football Australia |date=5 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=16 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230316095115/https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-comfortably-defeat-north-mariana-islands-shepparton-opener |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Webb |first=Daniel |title='It was amazing': Nestory Irankunda stars on Australian debut |url=https://www.sheppnews.com.au/sport/it-was-amazing-nestory-irankunda-stars-on-australian-debut/ |website=Shepparton News |date=6 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=14 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514022546/https://www.sheppnews.com.au/sport/it-was-amazing-nestory-irankunda-stars-on-australian-debut/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored three more goals in the remaining group games, with one against [[Cambodia national under-17 football team|Cambodia]] (10–0)<ref>{{cite web |title=Subway Joeys stay top with ten-goal Cambodia victory |url=https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-stay-top-ten-goal-cambodia-victory |publisher=Football Australia |date=7 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=16 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230316094956/https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-stay-top-ten-goal-cambodia-victory |url-status=live }}</ref> and two against [[China national under-17 football team|China]] (3–1).<ref>{{cite web |title=Subway Joeys secure automatic qualification to next year's AFC U17 Asian Cup with win over China |url=https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-secure-automatic-qualification-next-years-afc-u17-asian-cuptm-win-over-china |publisher=Football Australia |date=9 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=8 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308072758/https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-joeys-secure-automatic-qualification-next-years-afc-u17-asian-cuptm-win-over-china |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Kleeman |first=James |title=Nestory Irankunda bolsters stocks after stellar qualifying campaign |url=https://www.sheppnews.com.au/sport/nestory-irankunda-bolsters-stocks-after-stellar-qualifying-campaign/ |url-access=subscription |website=Shepparton News |date=10 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023}}</ref> Irankunda performances helped Australia in topping the group and qualifying for the [[AFC U-17 Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adelaide United's teenage sensation leads Joeys to 2023 AFC U17 Asian Cup |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/irankunda-at-the-double-as-joeys-qualify-for-2023-afc-u17-asian-cup/ |website=keepup.com |date=9 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517095418/https://keepup.com.au/news/irankunda-at-the-double-as-joeys-qualify-for-2023-afc-u17-asian-cup/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 May 2023, Irankunda was added to the Australia squad set to play in the [[2023 AFC U-17 Asian Cup]] hosted in [[Thailand]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda headlines exciting Joeys squad for U17 Asian Cup |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/socceroos-joeys-squad-u17-asian-cup-irankunda-a-league-men/ |website=keepup.com |date=16 May 2023 |access-date=19 June 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065503/https://aleagues.com.au/alumni/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=Irankunda & A-Leagues headline Joeys' Asian Cup squad |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-asian-cup-a-leagues-football-news/ |website=keepup.com |publisher=Isuzu UTE A-League |date=12 June 2023 |access-date=19 June 2023 |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614020112/https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-asian-cup-a-leagues-football-news/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 June 2023, in the second round of the group stage, Irankunda scored twice in 18 minutes of a 5–3 win over [[China national under-17 football team|China]].<ref>{{cite web |title=WATCH: Joeys prevail over China in AFC U17 Asian Cup epic |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/watch-joeys-prevail-over-china-afc-u17-asian-cup-epic |publisher=Socceroos |date=19 June 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=19 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230619165212/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/watch-joeys-prevail-over-china-afc-u17-asian-cup-epic |url-status=live }}</ref> His second goal, a powerful long-range strike, garnered widespread attention on social media due to its audacity and quality.<ref>{{cite web |title=Watch: Irankunda's scintillating 18-minute AFC Under-17 Asian Cup brace |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/watch-irankundas-scintillating-18-minute-afc-under-17-asian-cup-brace/ |website=keepup.com |date=19 June 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=19 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230619224819/https://keepup.com.au/news/watch-irankundas-scintillating-18-minute-afc-under-17-asian-cup-brace/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Joeys' U17 Asian Cup group-stage review: Top performers, what to improve & Japan challenge |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-u17-asian-cup-group-stage-review-top-performers-what-to-improve-japan-challenge/ |website=keepup.com |date=24 June 2023 |access-date=25 June 2023 |archive-date=25 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230625021942/https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-u17-asian-cup-group-stage-review-top-performers-what-to-improve-japan-challenge/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda scored in Australia's last game as his side were knocked out by [[Japan national under-17 football team|Japan]] following a 3–1 defeat in the [[2023 AFC U-17 Asian Cup#Quarter-finals|knockout stage]].<ref>{{cite web |title=WATCH: Australia's AFC U17 Asian Cup campaign ends in defeat to Japan |url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/japan-u17-vs-australia-u17-match-report |publisher=Socceroos |date=26 June 2023 |access-date=26 June 2023 |archive-date=9 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231209123711/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/japan-u17-vs-australia-u17-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Cup lift and our internationals can boost us: Andrioli |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/cup-lift-and-our-internationals-can-boost-us-andrioli |publisher=Adelaide United |date=22 June 2023 |access-date=26 June 2023 |archive-date=28 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230628032455/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/cup-lift-and-our-internationals-can-boost-us-andrioli |url-status=live }}</ref>

In April 2024, Irankunda was omitted from the [[Australia men's national under-23 soccer team|Australia national under-23 team]] that was set to compete in the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]], in contention to qualify for the [[2024 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Brunsdon |first=Simon |title=Superstar $5.8m teen snubbed for Olympic qualifiers |url=https://wwos.nine.com.au/olympics/football-news-2024-olyroos-squad-nestory-irankunda-snubbed-team-paris/d36bc5c0-98f2-4482-874b-557f69db6838 |publisher=Nine News |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024 |archive-date=4 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240404051222/https://wwos.nine.com.au/olympics/football-news-2024-olyroos-squad-nestory-irankunda-snubbed-team-paris/d36bc5c0-98f2-4482-874b-557f69db6838 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Irankunda omitted as Olyroos aim for Paris berth |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/39869664/nestory-irankunda-omitted-olyroos-squad-paris-berth-line |website=ESPN |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=3 April 2024 |archive-date=4 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240404020804/https://www.espn.com.au/football/story/_/id/39869664/nestory-irankunda-omitted-olyroos-squad-paris-berth-line |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Cootes |first=Isabel |title='Bigger picture' outlook behind Nestory Irankunda's Olyroos Olympic qualifying squad absence |url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/socceroos/os72522/nestory-irankunda-olyroos-asian-cup-squad-vidmar-adelaide-bayern-munich-paris-2024 |publisher=Optus Sport |access-date=4 April 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240404053503/https://sport.optus.com.au/news/socceroos/os72522/nestory-irankunda-olyroos-asian-cup-squad-vidmar-adelaide-bayern-munich-paris-2024 |archive-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024}}</ref> Coach [[Tony Vidmar]] stated his absence was in concern over his maturity and to prevent further "damage" from pressure.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title='We don't want to damage him': Vidmar explains Irankunda Olympic snub |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-snubbed-as-olyroos-squad-named-for-paris-2024-qualifiers-20240403-p5fh2c.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=4 April 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240404000006/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-snubbed-as-olyroos-squad-named-for-paris-2024-qualifiers-20240403-p5fh2c.html |archive-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='Hate to be in his shoes': Olyroos coach's explanation for latest Irankunda snub |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2024-04-04/tony-vidmar-nestory-irankunda-olympics-u23-asia-cup-squad/103667878 |website=ABC News |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065503/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2024-04-04/tony-vidmar-nestory-irankunda-olympics-u23-asia-cup-squad/103667878 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='We have to look at the bigger picture': Nestory Irankunda left out of Australia's Olympic qualifiers |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/apr/04/under-23-asian-cup-olyroos-squad-marco-tilio-nestory-irankunda-olympic-games-qualifier |website=The Guardian |publisher=Australian Associated Press |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=4 April 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065502/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/apr/04/under-23-asian-cup-olyroos-squad-marco-tilio-nestory-irankunda-olympic-games-qualifier |url-status=live }}</ref> However, after [[Marco Tilio]] sustained an injury,<ref>{{cite web |last=Harrington |first=Anna |title=Melbourne City – and Olyroos – sweat on Tilio injury |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8582527/melbourne-city-and-olyroos-sweat-on-tilio-injury/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=8 April 2024 |date=6 April 2024 |archive-date=8 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240408214755/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8582527/melbourne-city-and-olyroos-sweat-on-tilio-injury/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda was offered a spot but declined to play his [[2023–24 Adelaide United FC season|remaining club fixtures]] for [[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title=Irankunda declines approach to join Olyroos for Paris 2024 qualifiers |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-declines-approach-to-join-olyroos-for-paris-2024-qualifiers-20240408-p5fi9u.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=8 April 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240408214158/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-declines-approach-to-join-olyroos-for-paris-2024-qualifiers-20240408-p5fi9u.html |archive-date=8 April 2024 |date=8 April 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Football prodigy rejects Olyroos approach |url=https://wwos.nine.com.au/olympics/football-news-2024-nestory-irankunda-olyroos-approach-revealed/f62dc5d9-6146-4672-941b-5dd358f0c1d6 |publisher=Nine News |access-date=9 April 2024 |date=9 April 2024 |archive-date=9 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240409032037/https://wwos.nine.com.au/olympics/football-news-2024-nestory-irankunda-olyroos-approach-revealed/f62dc5d9-6146-4672-941b-5dd358f0c1d6 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Keegan Jelacic]] was called up instead in place of Tilio.<ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=ALM duo into Olyroos squad as Irankunda turns down call |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8585955/alm-duo-into-olyroos-squad-as-irankunda-turns-down-call/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=9 April 2024 |date=9 April 2024 |archive-date=9 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240409204949/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8585955/alm-duo-into-olyroos-squad-as-irankunda-turns-down-call/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |title=Nestory Irankunda having agency over his future is a good thing for Australian football |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2024/apr/10/nestory-irankunda-having-agency-over-his-future-is-a-good-thing-for-australian-football |website=The Guardian |access-date=9 April 2024 |date=9 April 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065505/https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2024/apr/10/nestory-irankunda-having-agency-over-his-future-is-a-good-thing-for-australian-football |url-status=live }}</ref> As a result of his last-minute response, and criticism from two [[A-League]] clubs, [[Football Australia]] conducted an independent review to suspend Irankunda from domestic competitions during the entirety of Australia's campaign according to regulations for declining.<ref>{{cite web |title=ALM clubs air grievances over Irankunda's Olyroos snub |url=https://www.sheppnews.com.au/aap-soccer/alm-clubs-air-grievances-over-irankundas-olyroos-snub/ |website=Shepparton News |publisher=Australian Associated Press |access-date=13 April 2024 |date=11 April 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065615/https://www.sheppnews.com.au/aap-soccer/alm-clubs-air-grievances-over-irankundas-olyroos-snub/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Migliaccio |first=Val |title='Get the full story': Adelaide boss fumes as rivals' plot to ban teen star over Olyroos snub revealed |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/get-the-full-story-adelaide-boss-fumes-as-rivals-plot-to-ban-teen-star-over-olyroos-snub-revealed/news-story/552d8bca986214be4b486d3f13cfa34d |website=Fox Sports |access-date=13 April 2024 |date=13 April 2024 |archive-date=15 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240415055341/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/get-the-full-story-adelaide-boss-fumes-as-rivals-plot-to-ban-teen-star-over-olyroos-snub-revealed/news-story/552d8bca986214be4b486d3f13cfa34d |url-status=live }}</ref> However, Irankunda was confirmed to be available for club selection since he was not formally called-up by Vidmar,<ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=Anna Harrington, Joanna Guelas and George |title=Irankunda cleared to play for Adelaide after FA review |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8590398/irankunda-cleared-to-play-for-adelaide-after-fa-review/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=13 April 2024 |date=12 April 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065614/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8590398/irankunda-cleared-to-play-for-adelaide-after-fa-review/ |url-status=live }}</ref> or held no apparent conversation with [[Football Australia]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Rayson |first=Zac |title=Olympics on the line in Olyroos' massive U-23 cup… but one big problem could ruin Paris dream |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/socceroos/asian-u23-cup-football-news-2024-paris-olympics-football-qualifying-olyroos-socceroos-nestory-irankunda/news-story/78ab496c781fa6410eedf54667ae16c0 |work=Fox Sports |access-date=16 April 2024 |date=15 April 2024 |archive-date=15 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240415194511/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/socceroos/asian-u23-cup-football-news-2024-paris-olympics-football-qualifying-olyroos-socceroos-nestory-irankunda/news-story/78ab496c781fa6410eedf54667ae16c0 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the conclusion of the tournament, it was reported that Irankunda's omission was under review by Football Australia after the ''Olyroos'' failed to qualify without scoring a single goal.<ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Irankunda omission to form part of FA's Olyroos review |url=https://www.illawarramercury.com.au/story/8600055/irankunda-omission-to-form-part-of-fas-olyroos-review/ |website=Illawarra Mercury |access-date=24 April 2024 |date=22 April 2024 |archive-date=24 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240424060212/https://www.illawarramercury.com.au/story/8600055/irankunda-omission-to-form-part-of-fas-olyroos-review/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Irankunda was called up to the [[Australia men's national under-20 soccer team|Australia national under-20 team]] team on 22 May 2025 for two friendlies against [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina]] as part of preparations for the [[2025 FIFA U-20 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/young-socceroos-squad-argentina-fixtures-confirmed|title=Young Socceroos squad for Argentina fixtures confirmed|website=Socceroos|date=22 May 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250527075733/https://www.socceroos.com.au/news/young-socceroos-squad-argentina-fixtures-confirmed|archive-date=27 May 2025|url-status=live}}</ref> however, he withdrew from the squad on 1 June due to injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-young-socceroos-squad-update-argentina-friendlies|title=Subway Young Socceroos Squad Update - Argentina Fixtures|website=Football Australia|date=1 June 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250601074713/https://www.footballaustralia.com.au/news/subway-young-socceroos-squad-update-argentina-friendlies|archive-date=1 June 2025|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 14 March 2023, Irankunda received his first international call-up to the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] squad, being named as a "train on" player for the [[friendly match|friendlies]] against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Monteverde |first=Marco |title=Nestory Irankunda feeling 'amazing' after being named as a train-on player with the Socceroos squad |url=https://www.news.com.au/sport/football/nestory-irankunda-feeling-amazing-after-being-named-as-a-trainon-player-with-the-socceroos-squad/news-story/04c4cbde1142a1ddae2ec5a98ecdad8f |website=news.com.au |date=14 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=15 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230315102021/https://www.news.com.au/sport/football/nestory-irankunda-feeling-amazing-after-being-named-as-a-trainon-player-with-the-socceroos-squad/news-story/04c4cbde1142a1ddae2ec5a98ecdad8f |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Slessor |first=Cameron |title=Why this teen sensation could become the youngest Socceroo in history |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-03-16/adelaide-united-nestory-irankunda-impresses-a-league-mens/102099100 |website=ABC News |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=15 March 2023 |archive-date=30 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240330161752/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2023-03-16/adelaide-united-nestory-irankunda-impresses-a-league-mens/102099100 |url-status=live }}</ref> During his time in the squad, he befriended [[Awer Mabil]], who called himself as the "big brother" and helped him settle in with the seniors. He also befriended youngster [[Garang Kuol]] who had experienced a similar journey through the A-League.<ref name="sydneymorning"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda has been given the perfect Socceroos roommate: He'll be a 'big brother' |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-has-been-given-the-perfect-socceroos-roommate-hell-be-a-big-brother/ |website=keepup.com |date=21 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517095417/https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-has-been-given-the-perfect-socceroos-roommate-hell-be-a-big-brother/ |url-status=live }}</ref> As a result of [[Riley McGree]] falling ill during his travel to [[Sydney]], Irankunda was included in the match squad in both matches against Ecuador.<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda in for Socceroos as Riley McGree sidelined |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8132664/irankunda-in-for-socceroos-as-riley-mcgree-sidelined/ |website=The Canberra Times |date=23 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517095415/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8132664/irankunda-in-for-socceroos-as-riley-mcgree-sidelined/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Although he could have potentially become the youngest player to appear for the Socceroos, surpassing [[Duncan Cummings]]' record, he did not feature in either match.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kemp |first=Emma |title=Socceroos call up 17-year-old sensation Nestory Irankunda for Ecuador friendlies |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/23/socceroos-call-up-17-year-old-sensation-nestory-irankunda-for-ecuador-friendlies |website=[[The Guardian]] |date=23 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=23 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230323065114/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/23/socceroos-call-up-17-year-old-sensation-nestory-irankunda-for-ecuador-friendlies |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title='We have to let him grow': Socceroos urge patience with 17-year-old 'freak' |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/we-have-to-let-him-grow-socceroos-urge-patience-with-17-year-old-freak-20230321-p5ctzh.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230322004034/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/we-have-to-let-him-grow-socceroos-urge-patience-with-17-year-old-freak-20230321-p5ctzh.html |archive-date=22 March 2023 |date=21 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023}}</ref>

In November, the [[Football Federation of Burundi|Burundi Football Association]] announced their interest in Irankunda to represent their [[Burundi national football team|national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Burundi hope to woo Bayern Munich-bound wonderkid |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67426146 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=17 November 2023 |date=17 November 2023 |archive-date=16 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231116195454/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67426146 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2024, Irankunda stated, that despite pursuing a debut with Australia, he would consider playing for either Burundi or [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]] if [[Graham Arnold]] continues to exclude him in future tournaments.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vinall |first1=Marnie |last2=Harrington |first2=Anna |title=Irankunda wants Socceroos call-up; Matildas stars escape exhibition match unscathed |url=https://www.theage.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-wants-socceroos-call-up-but-won-t-rule-out-international-switch-20240524-p5jgix.html |website=The Age |access-date=25 May 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240525002924/https://www.theage.com.au/sport/soccer/irankunda-wants-socceroos-call-up-but-won-t-rule-out-international-switch-20240524-p5jgix.html |archive-date=25 May 2024 |date=24 May 2024}}</ref> On 29 May, days after his comments, Irankunda was called-up to the Australian national team ahead of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2026 World Cup qualification]] matches in June against [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh]] and [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda selected in Socceroos Squad for Final Round Two World Cup Qualifiers |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-selected-in-socceroos-squad-for-final-round-two-world-cup-qualifiers/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=29 May 2024 |date=29 May 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065615/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-selected-in-socceroos-squad-for-final-round-two-world-cup-qualifiers/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Arnold expressed that he was surprised by Irankunda's consideration to play for other national teams but praised his maturity following his omission in the Olyroos squad.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title='He's got the quality – now it's time for him to show it': Socceroos coach throws down gauntlet to Irankunda |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/remember-me-former-whiz-kid-arzani-returns-in-new-look-socceroos-squad-20240529-p5jhic.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=29 May 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240529103433/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/remember-me-former-whiz-kid-arzani-returns-in-new-look-socceroos-squad-20240529-p5jhic.html |archive-date=29 May 2024 |date=29 May 2024}}</ref> However, after the first training session in [[Dhaka]], Arnold said the issues were "for a headline" and has been resolved.<ref>{{cite web |last=Rugari |first=Vince |title='Do that for the nation': Socceroos to unleash Bayern Munich-bound young gun |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/do-that-for-the-nation-socceroos-to-unleash-bayern-munich-bound-young-gun-20240605-p5jjdq.html |website=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=6 June 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240605060946/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/do-that-for-the-nation-socceroos-to-unleash-bayern-munich-bound-young-gun-20240605-p5jjdq.html |archive-date=5 June 2024 |date=5 June 2024}}</ref>

Irankunda started on his international debut on 6 June, providing an assist in the opening goal to [[Ajdin Hrustic]], in a 2–0 win against [[Bangladesh national football team|Bangladesh]] during [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Harrington |first=Anna |title=Plenty to come from Irankunda after Socceroos debut |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8654881/plenty-to-come-from-irankunda-after-socceroos-debut/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=6 June 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240606221613/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8654881/plenty-to-come-from-irankunda-after-socceroos-debut/ |archive-date=6 June 2024 |date=6 June 2024}}</ref> Five days later, Irankunda scored his first goal for the ''Socceroos'' from a penalty in a 5–0 victory against Palestine.<ref>{{cite web |last=Monteverde |first=Marco |title=Teen sensation scores first Socceroos goal as Aussies thrash minnows |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/teen-sensation-scores-first-socceroos-goal-as-aussies-thrash-minnows/news-story/09172e3d540d2ee45736e1ad92b710bc |website=Fox Sports |publisher=NCA NewsWire |access-date=11 June 2024 |date=11 June 2024 |archive-date=12 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240612090646/https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/teen-sensation-scores-first-socceroos-goal-as-aussies-thrash-minnows/news-story/09172e3d540d2ee45736e1ad92b710bc |url-status=live }}</ref> At the age of 18 years and 123 days, he became the second youngest player to score for Australia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda becomes second-youngest Socceroos scorer: All-time leaderboard |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/australia-5-0-palestine-match-report-nestory-irankunda-goal-perth-hbf-park-goals-highlights-video/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=11 June 2024 |date=11 June 2024 |archive-date=12 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240612090647/https://aleagues.com.au/news/australia-5-0-palestine-match-report-nestory-irankunda-goal-perth-hbf-park-goals-highlights-video/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Style of play===
{{quote box |align=right |salign=right |width=33% |quote="He can do things on a pitch that I haven’t seen other players do. So explosive. In training games, he’ll have three four-minute spells when no-one wants to go near him."|author={{mdash}}[[Carl Veart|Veart]] on Irankunda's playing style in training{{r|codesports}}}}
Irankunda is regarded by many within the Australian media as one of the greatest talents developed in the country.<ref name="sydneymorning"/><ref name="canberratimes"/><ref name="keepup1"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Every word of Aloisi's stunning praise for prodigious Reds talent after career-first feat |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-john-aloisi-adelaide-united-hat-trick-press-conference-full-transcript/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=30 March 2024 |date=29 March 2024 |archive-date=30 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240330002108/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-john-aloisi-adelaide-united-hat-trick-press-conference-full-transcript/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His goal-scoring prowess received many plaudits from media and pundits who recognised his skills and techniques, and even compared his [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] goal against [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]] to that of [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda on the 'new technique' behind his emphatic 'Ronaldo-esque' stunner |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/he-doesnt-practice-tap-ins-just-worldies-nestory-irankunda-explains-his-ronaldo-esque-stunner/ |website=keepup.com |date=26 February 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517145241/https://keepup.com.au/news/he-doesnt-practice-tap-ins-just-worldies-nestory-irankunda-explains-his-ronaldo-esque-stunner/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His ability to draw fouls from opponents, albeit too frequently, led to Carl Veart demanding that referees protect the young prospect more and punish opposing players for tackles that could harm him.<ref>{{cite web |last=Monteverde |first=Marco |title=Adelaide United teenager Nestory Irankunda 'frustrated' with on-field treatment |url=https://www.news.com.au/sport/football/adelaide-united-teenager-nestory-irankunda-frustrated-with-onfield-treatment/news-story/ea0f2dc5572e9738465719bd64c67339 |website=news.com.au |date=4 March 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=4 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230504231812/https://www.news.com.au/sport/football/adelaide-united-teenager-nestory-irankunda-frustrated-with-onfield-treatment/news-story/ea0f2dc5572e9738465719bd64c67339 |url-status=live }}</ref> In his breakthrough season, Veart's protection of Irankunda led to restriction of minutes on the pitch, having made all of his appearances off the bench, to ensure that the player develops properly.<ref>{{cite web |last=D'Urbano |first=Nick |title=Adelaide urged to make 'blockbuster' Irankunda call to answer 'massive, massive question' |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-men-news-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-united-central-coast-mariners/ |website=keepup.com |date=16 May 2023 |access-date=19 June 2023 |archive-date=19 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230619001119/https://keepup.com.au/news/a-league-men-news-nestory-irankunda-adelaide-united-central-coast-mariners/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Harrington |first=Anna |title=Adelaide ponder Irankunda start for Mariners final |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/adelaide-ponder-irankunda-start-for-mariners-final/ |website=keepup.com |date=20 May 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=19 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230619001117/https://keepup.com.au/news/adelaide-ponder-irankunda-start-for-mariners-final/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Deployed on the right wing by [[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]] manager [[Carl Veart]], Irankunda utilises his pace and dribbling to stretch the field wide and disrupt the opposition's tactics, effectively in the later stages of matches against fatigued opponents.<ref>{{cite web |title=Youth in focus: Ava Pritchard and Nestory Irankunda |url=https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/youth-in-focus-ava-pritchard-and-nestory-irankunda |website=Front Page Football |date=30 December 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517145243/https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/youth-in-focus-ava-pritchard-and-nestory-irankunda |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="sydneymorning"/> He adeptly takes the ball inside, using his dribbling skills to manoeuvre past opponents to open opportunities to shoot on goal or cross towards the centre.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mariners eye Grand Final berth after successfully nullifying Irankunda |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/australian-a-league-men/story/4947544/central-coast-mariners-eye-grand-final-berth-after-successfully-nullifying-nestory-irankunda |website=ESPN |date=14 May 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517145243/https://www.espn.com.au/football/australian-a-league-men/story/4947544/central-coast-mariners-eye-grand-final-berth-after-successfully-nullifying-nestory-irankunda |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda is known for his shot power on goal and often opts to shoot rather than pass when inside the goal area.<ref name="codesports"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Thomas |first=Stuart |title=Teenage sensation Nestory Irankunda should resist overseas overtures and remain in the A-League - for now |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2023/03/14/teenage-sensation-nestory-irankunda-should-resist-overseas-overtures-and-remain-in-the-a-league-for-now/ |website=The Roar |date=13 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517145248/https://www.theroar.com.au/2023/03/14/teenage-sensation-nestory-irankunda-should-resist-overseas-overtures-and-remain-in-the-a-league-for-now/ |url-status=live }}</ref> However, after gaining regular playing time in the [[2023–24 Adelaide United FC season|2023–24 season]], Irankunda played a more creative and mature role which used his pace, dribbling and weaker foot to cut inside and lay off striking opportunities for forwards more frequently. In a [[Formation (association football)|4–3–3 formation]], he would rotate between either wing of the field or directly in the centre to create goal-scoring opportunities.<ref>{{cite web |last=Marchetti |first=Christian |title=The subtle signs that Nestory Irankunda's development is accelerating |url=https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/the-subtle-signs-that-nestory-irankunda-s-development-is-accelerating |website=Front Page Football |access-date=19 May 2024 |date=4 April 2024 |archive-date=19 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240519223235/https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/the-subtle-signs-that-nestory-irankunda-s-development-is-accelerating |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Reception ===
{{quote box
| align = right
| salign = right
| width = 33%
| quote = "At his age, I only saw Messi and him at this level. The power, the skills. Never in my life at 17 years of age have I seen a player like him and Messi"
| author = {{mdash}}[[Javi López (footballer, born 1986)|López]] on Irankunda{{r|reception1}}
}}

With his consistent and impressive performances since his breakthrough season, Irankunda has received praise from his teammate [[Javi López (footballer, born 1986)|Javi López]], who compared his development with Argentine footballer [[Lionel Messi]] at the age of 17.<ref name="reception1">{{cite web |title='Only him and Messi': Extraordinary tip-off agents are receiving about Nestory Irankunda |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-lionel-messi-a-league-adelaide-united-javi-lopez/ |website=keepup.com |date=3 May 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=17 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230517145240/https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-lionel-messi-a-league-adelaide-united-javi-lopez/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Many coaches, including international managers, who had witnessed Irankunda play have agreed with this sentiment.<ref>{{cite web |last=Comito |first=Matt |title=Rival coaches' interesting Irankunda insight: 'It's good for Asian football as a whole' |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-australia-u17-asian-cup-2023-preview-dates-kick-off-broadcast-details/ |website=keepup.com |date=15 June 2023 |access-date=20 June 2023 |archive-date=18 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230618232331/https://keepup.com.au/news/joeys-australia-u17-asian-cup-2023-preview-dates-kick-off-broadcast-details/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda has also been compared to [[Alphonso Davies]] for their similar journey in football; Davies was born in a refugee camp in Ghana before residing in Canada.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kershaw |first=Tom |title=Meet Nestory Irankunda: from refugee camp to Bayern Munich |url=https://www.thetimes.com/world/australasia/article/nestory-irankunda-from-refugee-camp-to-bayern-munich-xtnzqnt75 |work=[[The Times]] |access-date=14 January 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20231114183352/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/nestory-irankunda-from-refugee-camp-to-bayern-munich-xtnzqnt75 |archive-date=14 November 2023 |url-status=live |date=14 November 2023}}</ref>

Irankunda is recognised as a prominent figure of South Australian football, being named by [[Messenger Newspapers]] as "one of the top 20 South Australian athletes to watch in 2023,"<ref>{{cite web |last=Renfrey |first=Daniel |title=The Messenger names top 20 young South Australian athletes to watch in 2023 |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/messenger/sport/the-messenger-names-top-20-young-south-australian-athletes-to-watch-in-2023/news-story/2cbec473d52ddcadf703222e7f46c055?amp&nk=3bbf36a8fd02236ba14e7c178ab0e669-1705315816 |website=The Advertiser |publisher=The Messenger |access-date=15 January 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240115105008/https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/messenger/sport/the-messenger-names-top-20-young-south-australian-athletes-to-watch-in-2023/news-story/2cbec473d52ddcadf703222e7f46c055?amp&nk=3bbf36a8fd02236ba14e7c178ab0e669-1705315816 |archive-date=15 January 2024 |date=13 February 2023}}</ref> and listed on 5 January 2024 by [[The Advertiser (Adelaide)|The Advertiser]] as "one of the 24 South Australians to watch in 2024".<ref>{{cite web |last=Polymeneas |first=Evangeline |title=The 24 South Australians to watch in 2024 |url=https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/the-24-south-australians-to-watch-in-2024/news-story/6a2d8ecb8bdd88416a3d95cfd81b75b1?amp&nk=1c49006adeccebef2cb8866e0f29de30-1704485835 |website=Adelaide Now |publisher=The Advertiser |access-date=29 January 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240105201705/https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/the-24-south-australians-to-watch-in-2024/news-story/6a2d8ecb8bdd88416a3d95cfd81b75b1?amp&nk=1c49006adeccebef2cb8866e0f29de30-1704485835 |archive-date=5 January 2024 |date=5 January 2024}}</ref> On 11 October 2023, Irankunda was named as one of the 60 best young talents in world football by ''[[The Guardian]]'', being the only Australian listed, among other talents like [[Endrick (footballer, born 2006)|Endrick]], [[Warren Zaïre-Emery]], [[Paris Brunner]], and [[Simone Pafundi]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Christenson |first1=Marcus |last2=Bloor |first2=Steven |last3=Blight |first3=Garry |title=Next Generation 2023: 60 of the best young talents in world football |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football |website=The Guardian |access-date=15 October 2023 |date=11 October 2023 |archive-date=5 February 2024 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20240205141455/https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/oct/11/next-generation-2023-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Where are they now? Every Aussie to be named on Guardian's top 60 as Irankunda makes 2023 list |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-nestory-irankunda-next-gen-top-60-botic-caputo-western-united-melbourne-city/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=15 October 2023 |date=12 October 2023 |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018074955/https://aleagues.com.au/news/adelaide-united-nestory-irankunda-next-gen-top-60-botic-caputo-western-united-melbourne-city/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In March 2024, Irankunda was ranked among the best 50 young talents born after January 2005 in the annual NXGN lists from [[Goal (website)|GOAL]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=17yo sensation one of two A-Leagues stars named among world's 50 best young footballers |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-nestory-irankunda-daniela-galic-adelaide-melb-city-nxgn-2024-bayern-munich-news/ |website=A-League |access-date=21 March 2024 |date=19 March 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065506/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-nestory-irankunda-daniela-galic-adelaide-melb-city-nxgn-2024-bayern-munich-news/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda named Goal's NxGN Best 50 wonderkids |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-named-goals-nxgn-best-50-wonderkids/ |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=27 March 2024 |date=26 March 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065618/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-named-goals-nxgn-best-50-wonderkids/ |url-status=live }}</ref> [[L'Équipe]] also listed Irankunda in a similar category list of 30 players in June.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nestory Irankunda named in prestigious list of the best U20 players in world football |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-lequipe-top-30-players-under-20-world-football-lamal-endrick-full-list/ |publisher=A-Leagues |access-date=9 June 2024 |date=7 June 2024 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065508/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-lequipe-top-30-players-under-20-world-football-lamal-endrick-full-list/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

As one of the youngest members of Adelaide United's squad at the time, Irankunda was subject to criticism for his "emotional outbursts" and lack of maturity on the football pitch,<ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Irate Irankunda needs to cool his fiery streak: Veart |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/irate-irankunda-needs-to-cool-his-fiery-streak-veart-592797 |website=FTBL |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=1 April 2023 |archive-date=14 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114153426/https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/irate-irankunda-needs-to-cool-his-fiery-streak-veart-592797 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Fiery outbursts may cost Irankunda Australia call-ups |url=https://www.thecourier.com.au/story/8413510/fiery-outbursts-may-cost-irankunda-australia-call-ups/ |website=The Courier |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=6 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008065509/https://www.thecourier.com.au/story/8413510/fiery-outbursts-may-cost-irankunda-australia-call-ups/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Harper |first=Lachlan |title=Aussie wonderkid in tears after brutal subbing |url=https://wwos.nine.com.au/football/a-league-news-2023-nestory-irankunda-crying-bayern-munich-move/f15e1357-f681-4335-9b70-4deb9bfe0560 |publisher=Nine News |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=10 December 2023 |archive-date=22 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231222155103/https://wwos.nine.com.au/football/a-league-news-2023-nestory-irankunda-crying-bayern-munich-move/f15e1357-f681-4335-9b70-4deb9bfe0560 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda reaction sparks 'important' conversation as Adelaide boss responds: 'That's all it is' |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-news-a-league-talking-points-bruno-fornaroli-socceroos-asian-cup/ |website=A-Leagues |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=10 December 2023 |archive-date=22 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231222155109/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-news-a-league-talking-points-bruno-fornaroli-socceroos-asian-cup/ |url-status=live }}</ref> which gained attention from his [[Fouls and misconduct (association football)|send-off]] in the match against Melbourne Victory in November 2023.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Irankunda send-off debate: the 'bigger context' to red card |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/official-isuzu-ute-aleague-talking-points-round-3-irankunda-velupillay-ikonomidis-zawada/ |website=A-Leagues |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=7 November 2023 |archive-date=14 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114153427/https://aleagues.com.au/news/official-isuzu-ute-aleague-talking-points-round-3-irankunda-velupillay-ikonomidis-zawada/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Pagonis |first=Antonis |title=How did Adelaide United's young charges fare against original rivals Melbourne Victory? |url=https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/how-did-adelaide-united-s-young-charges-fare-against-original-rivals-melbourne-victory |website=Front Page Football |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=6 November 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008070013/https://www.frontpagefootball.net/post/how-did-adelaide-united-s-young-charges-fare-against-original-rivals-melbourne-victory |url-status=live }}</ref> Veart stated that the winger has been working on his frustrations and needs to be able to control his emotions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Veart: 'We're disappointed at the end of the game to finish one-all' |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-were-disappointed-at-the-end-of-the-game-to-finish-one-all |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=5 November 2023 |archive-date=16 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231116093219/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/veart-were-disappointed-at-the-end-of-the-game-to-finish-one-all |url-status=live }}</ref> Bayern Munich sporting director Christoph Freund stated the club were aware of this, adding that due to his young age, "it’s better when the boys are involved with heart and passion."<ref>{{cite web |last=Pisani |first=Sacha |title=Bayern Munich respond to Irankunda moment in the A-Leagues: 'It's better when...' |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/bayern-munich-nestory-irankunda-a-league-bundesliga-news/ |website=KEEPUP |publisher=A-League |access-date=29 January 2024 |date=12 December 2023 |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008070013/https://aleagues.com.au/news/bayern-munich-nestory-irankunda-a-league-bundesliga-news/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Irankunda would show improvement into the new year and received praise from Veart after displaying calmness and maturity during the later matches of the [[2023–24 Adelaide United FC season|2023–24 season]], adding that "he's making good strides in that maturity."<ref>{{cite web |last=Clarke |first=George |title=Veart lauds Irankunda's improved maturity for Reds |url=https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8485335/veart-lauds-irankundas-improved-maturity-for-reds/ |website=The Canberra Times |access-date=14 January 2024 |date=13 January 2024 |archive-date=13 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240113191536/https://www.canberratimes.com.au/story/8485335/veart-lauds-irankundas-improved-maturity-for-reds/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Irankunda attended [[Parafield Gardens High School]] in [[Parafield Gardens, South Australia]], a northern suburb of [[Adelaide]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adelaide United's teenage sensations, balancing school work with professional football |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2023/03/23/adelaide-uniteds-teenage-sensations-balancing-school-work-with-professional-football/ |website=The Roar |date=22 March 2023 |access-date=18 May 2023 |archive-date=20 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230420073227/https://www.theroar.com.au/2023/03/23/adelaide-uniteds-teenage-sensations-balancing-school-work-with-professional-football/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite claiming to do poorly at school,<ref name="keepup2"/> Irankunda stated his favourite subject was [[English studies|English]], and enjoyed the [[Harry Potter|Harry Potter books series]] and [[Harry Potter (film series)|film series]].<ref name="keepup"/> He came runners-up in his category in the School Sports Awards in December 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=School Sports Awards |url=https://www.education.sa.gov.au/parents-and-families/curriculum-and-learning/school-sport-sa/awards2/school-sports-awards |publisher=[[Department for Education (South Australia)|Department for Education South Australia]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230521033341/https://www.education.sa.gov.au/parents-and-families/curriculum-and-learning/school-sport-sa/awards2/school-sports-awards |archive-date=21 May 2023 |date=14 October 2022 |access-date=18 May 2023}}</ref>

Irankunda supported Spanish club [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and idolised [[Carles Puyol]] and [[Gerard Piqué]], who influenced him to play centre-back as a child before converting to a more attacking role by his coaches.<ref name="keepup">{{cite web |last=D'Urbano |first=Nick |title=Nestory Irankunda has already mapped out his entire career after position swap 'out of nowhere' |url=https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-bayern-a-league-adelaide-united-feature/ |website=keepup.com |publisher=Isuzu UTE A-League |date=13 June 2023 |access-date=19 June 2023 |archive-date=14 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614014925/https://keepup.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-bayern-a-league-adelaide-united-feature/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He modelled his playing style on [[Lionel Messi]] for his agility and power.<ref name="keepup2"/> Despite his support for Barcelona, his father's long-time support for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], since his time in Africa,<ref name="ref1"/> influenced his decision to sign for the German club.<ref name="keepup2"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Irankunda: The talk of global football |url=https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-the-talk-of-global-football |publisher=Adelaide United |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=15 November 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115092101/https://adelaideunited.com.au/news/irankunda-the-talk-of-global-football |url-status=live }}</ref> In an interview in June 2023, Irankunda expressed his desire to retire with Adelaide United by the end of his career.<ref>{{cite web |last=D'Urbano |first=Nick |title=How a move 'out of nowhere' made Irankunda the player he is today: 'I was pretty upset when they told me' |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-bayern-a-league-adelaide-united-feature/ |publisher=A-League |access-date=15 November 2023 |date=13 June 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115022830/https://aleagues.com.au/news/nestory-irankunda-transfer-news-bayern-a-league-adelaide-united-feature/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

During his upbringing, Irankunda's father drove him around to his football games before he was old enough to obtain his driver's licence, and his older brothers stopped playing football to help pay for his football fees when he played in [[National Premier Leagues|NPL]].<ref name="keepup"/><ref>{{cite web |title=Making sure their community can afford football: our night out at an extraordinary event |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-african-all-stars-adelaide-mohamed-toure-dukuly-yengi-mabil/ |website=A-League |date=21 June 2023 |first=Matt |last=Comito |access-date=25 June 2023 |archive-date=31 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240331080204/https://aleagues.com.au/news/a-league-african-all-stars-adelaide-mohamed-toure-dukuly-yengi-mabil/ |url-status=live }}</ref> For this reason, he considers his father and brothers as his heroes, as well as his mother and sisters, who took care of him when he was a baby.<ref name="keepup"/> Irankunda is close friends with fellow professional footballer, [[Mohamed Toure (soccer, born 2004)|Mohamed Toure]], who has described him as "football [[Harry Houdini|Houdini]]" and "Australian [[Jude Bellingham]]".<ref>{{cite web |last=Lewis |first=Dave |title='He's a Houdini': Breakthrough Socceroo tips Irankunda to star in Europe |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/hes-a-houdini-breakthrough-socceroo-tips-irankunda-to-star-in-europe-602832 |website=FTBL |access-date=28 November 2023 |date=27 November 2023 |archive-date=30 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130074258/https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/hes-a-houdini-breakthrough-socceroo-tips-irankunda-to-star-in-europe-602832 |url-status=live }}</ref>

